    "df = pd.DataFrame(data=dataset.data,columns=dataset.feature_names)\n",
    "df[\"target\"] = dataset.target\n",
    "df.head()"
   ]

   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "((569, 30), (569, 1))"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 5,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "X = df[dataset.feature_names].values\n",
    "y = df[\"target\"].values.reshape(-1,1)\n",
    "\n",
    "X.shape, y.shape"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def linear_model_format_X(X):\n",
    "    if len(X.shape) == 1:\n",
    "        X = X.copy().reshape(-1,1)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return np.hstack(tup= ( np.ones(shape=(X.shape[0],1)) , X ) )"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Cost Function"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def entropy_cost_func(y_pred,y):\n",
    "    \n",
    "    part_1 = y * np.log(y_pred)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    part_2 = (1 - y) * np.log(1 - y_pred) \n",
    "    \n",
    "    cost = ( -1 / y_pred.shape[0] ) * np.sum(part_1 + part_2)   \n",
    "    return cost"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Sigmoid Function"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def sigmoid(z):\n",
    "    return 1 / (1 + np.exp(-z))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Gradient Descent Algorithm"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 53,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def logistic_regression_fit(X_i,y,alpha = 0.01,iterations = 10000):    \n",
    "    X = linear_model_format_X(X_i)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    n = X.shape[1]\n",
    "    m = y.shape[0]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    theta = np.random.rand(1,n)\n",
    "    print(\"random initial θ value :\",theta)\n",
    "\n",
    "    cost_history = []\n",
    "    theta_history = []\n",
    "\n",
    "    for iteration in range(iterations):\n",
    "\n",
    "        # calculate y_pred \n",
    "        y_pred = sigmoid(X @ theta.T) # (m,1) = (m,n) * (n,1)\n",
    "\n",
    "        # new θ to replace old θ\n",
    "        new_theta = np.zeros_like(theta)     \n",
    "\n",
    "        # simultaneous operation \n",
    "        new_theta = theta - (\n",
    "            alpha * np.sum( (y_pred - y ) * X , axis = 0 ) * (1/m)\n",
    "        )\n",
    "        \n",
    "\n",
    "        if np.isnan(np.sum(new_theta)) or np.isinf(np.sum(new_theta)):\n",
    "            print(\"breaking. found inf or nan.\")\n",
    "            break\n",
    "        # override new θ \n",
    "        theta = new_theta\n",
    "\n",
    "        # calculate cost to put in history\n",
    "        cost = entropy_cost_func( sigmoid(X @ theta.T), y)\n",
    "        cost_history.append(cost)\n",
    "\n",
    "        # calcualted theta in history\n",
    "        theta_history.append(theta[0])\n",
    "        \n",
    "    y_pred = sigmoid(X @ theta.T)\n",
    "    return X,y,y_pred,theta,theta_history,cost_history"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [

   "source": [
    "from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics import confusion_matrix,accuracy_score\n",
    "\n",
    "scaler = StandardScaler()\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "X_i = df[dataset.feature_names].values\n",
    "y = df[\"target\"].values.reshape(-1,1)\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "X_scaled = scaler.fit_transform(X_i)\n",
    "\n",
    "X,y,y_pred,theta,theta_history,cost_history = logistic_regression_fit( \n",
    "    X_i=X_scaled,\n",
    "    y=y,\n",
    "    alpha=0.003,\n",
    "    iterations=1000\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Fit theta :\",theta)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"\"\"\n",
    "Confusion Matrix : \n",
    "{confusion_matrix(y,y_pred>0.5)}\n",
    "Accuracy Score   : \n",
    "{accuracy_score(y,y_pred>0.5)}\n",
    "\"\"\")\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "fig = plt.figure(figsize=(10,10))\n",
    "ax = fig.add_subplot(2,2,1)\n",
    "ax.set(\n",
    "    xlabel=\"iterations\",\n",
    "    ylabel=\"loss :j(θ)\"\n",
    ")\n",
    "ax.plot(cost_history)\n",
    "ax.grid(alpha=0.5)\n",
    "\n",
    "ax = fig.add_subplot(2,2,2)\n",
    "ax.set(\n",
    "    xlabel=\"y_pred\",\n",
    "    ylabel=\"y\"\n",
    ")\n",
    "ax.scatter(y_pred,y)\n",
    "ax.grid(alpha=0.5)\n",
    "\n",
    "ax = fig.add_subplot(2,2,(3,4))\n",
    "ax.set(\n",
    "    ylabel=\"loss: j(θ)\",\n",
    "    xlabel=\"θ\"\n",
    ")\n",
    "ax.plot(theta_history,cost_history)\n",
    "ax.grid(alpha=0.5)\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n"
   ]

   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Logistic Regression with Regularization"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 54,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def logistic_regression_with_reg_fit(X_i,y,alpha = 0.01,iterations = 10000,penalty=0.1):    \n",
    "    X = linear_model_format_X(X_i)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    n = X.shape[1]\n",
    "    m = y.shape[0]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    theta = np.random.rand(1,n)\n",
    "    print(\"random initial θ value :\",theta)\n",
    "\n",
    "    cost_history = []\n",
    "    theta_history = []\n",
    "\n",
    "    for iteration in range(iterations):\n",
    "\n",
    "        # calculate y_pred \n",
    "        y_pred = sigmoid(X @ theta.T) # (m,1) = (m,n) * (n,1)\n",
    "\n",
    "        # new θ to replace old θ\n",
    "        new_theta = np.zeros_like(theta)     \n",
    "\n",
    "        # simultaneous operation \n",
    "        new_theta = theta - (\n",
    "            alpha * np.sum( (y_pred - y ) * X , axis = 0 ) * (1/m)\n",
    "        ) -  (penalty * theta * (1 / m) ) \n",
    "        \n",
    "\n",
    "        if np.isnan(np.sum(new_theta)) or np.isinf(np.sum(new_theta)):\n",
    "            print(\"breaking. found inf or nan.\")\n",
    "            break\n",
    "        # override new θ \n",
    "        theta = new_theta\n",
    "\n",
    "        # calculate cost to put in history\n",
    "        cost = entropy_cost_func( sigmoid(X @ theta.T), y)\n",
    "        cost_history.append(cost)\n",
    "\n",
    "        # calcualted theta in history\n",
    "        theta_history.append(theta[0])\n",
    "        \n",
    "    y_pred = sigmoid(X @ theta.T)\n",
    "    return X,y,y_pred,theta,theta_history,cost_history"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
